45:25.000 --> 45:28.000
If the absence of life in those remote parts of the world

45:28.000 --> 45:31.000
is explained by competition with existing forms of life,

45:31.000 --> 45:33.000
which is the more common explanation,

45:33.000 --> 45:36.000
then why is it so hard in a laboratory

45:36.000 --> 45:40.000
and of highly idealised conditions to synthesise life?

45:40.000 --> 45:42.000
Cool. Yeah, good. All good.

